  "texts": [
    "VMM core (Block 5)The voltages generated by each DAC (which represent the colour of each pixel of the rescaled n 2 × 1 image) are applied at the inputs (rows) of the n 2 × m crossbar array of memristors.",
    "The conductance of each memristor within the crossbar describes the synaptic connection between each input neuron (ith) and each output neuron (jth).",
    "This scheme is used in various papers 54,102.",
    "However, some others consider also a bias term added to the weighted sum fed to the neuron 57.",
    "This can be done digitally and off-chip, or in the analogue domain."
  ],
